 ✅ 2️⃣ Defect Traceability Matrix (DTM)

Now this is different 👇

 🔹 Definition

> Defect Traceability Matrix is a document that maps Defects ↔ Test Cases ↔ Requirements.

It helps track which requirement caused which defect.

---

 🧠 Easy Analogy – Hospital Example

Requirement = Healthy Body
Test Case = Medical Test
Defect = Disease Found

DTM tracks:

👉 Which test found which disease?
👉 Which body part (requirement) had problem?

---

2️⃣ DTM (Defect Traceability Matrix)

Now imagine:

After building house:

Bathroom tap is leaking

Bedroom window is broken

You write a record:

Which room has problem?

Who fixed it?

Is it fixed properly?

That record is DTM.

 🏢 Real-Time Example

Suppose:

| Req ID | Requirement         |
| ------ | ------------------- |
| R1     | Valid login         |
| R2     | Password validation |

Test Case TC2 fails and finds bug.

Bug ID = BUG101

---

 DTM Table:

| Bug ID | TC ID | Req ID | Status |
| ------ | ----- | ------ | ------ |
| BUG101 | TC2   | R2     | Open   |

Now we know:

 Bug belongs to R2
 Found by TC2
